  "name": "Morrison COU1 — ML hemolysis surrogate credibility assessment (CPB)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for an ML-based surrogate model trained to predict pump-induced hemolysis (relative hemolysis index, RH) for the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass conditions. The surrogate replaces full CFD evaluations for rapid design-space exploration across 5 flow-speed operating points. Validation evidence is drawn exclusively from a held-out test partition of the same experimental/CFD dataset used for training. No robustness characterization under input noise, covariate shift, or out-of-distribution operating conditions has been performed. COU1 evaluates whether the ML surrogate can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Medium",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
