      "acceptanceCriteria": "ML surrogate training pipeline under version control with documented hyperparameter configurations.",
      "rationale": "The gradient-boosted surrogate training code is maintained in a version-controlled repository (Git, tagged release v2.1.0). Hyperparameter configurations are logged via MLflow. Unit tests cover data preprocessing and feature engineering steps. Achieved level 2 exceeds the required level 1 for MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Surrogate training and inference routines verified against reference implementations on benchmark regression datasets.",
      "rationale": "The gradient boosting implementation (XGBoost v1.7) was verified against scikit-learn GradientBoostingRegressor on three standard regression benchmarks (Boston Housing, Ames Housing, synthetic sinusoidal). Relative prediction differences were below 0.5% across all benchmarks, confirming correct implementation of the learning algorithm."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "CFD-derived training labels generated at mesh density sufficient to achieve grid-converged RH values (GCI < 5%).",
      "rationale": "CFD simulations used to generate training labels employed a mesh of 4.2 million polyhedral cells. Grid convergence index (GCI) for RH was 2.8% between medium and fine mesh, satisfying the GCI < 5% criterion. The ML surrogate itself introduces no spatial discretization; this factor addresses the fidelity of the CFD labels used for training."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation test conditions span the five nominal flow-speed operating points specified in the COU.",
      "rationale": "The held-out test partition covers all five nominal flow-speed combinations (Q = 2, 3, 4, 5, 6 L/min; N = 2000, 2500, 3000, 3500, 4000 RPM) specified in the COU. Blood viscosity and density were fixed at 37°C physiological values consistent with the intended CPB operating environment. All test conditions are drawn from the same distribution as the training data."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "ML surrogate RH predictions compared against CFD-derived RH labels on test partition; MAE < 0.05 and R² > 0.95.",
      "rationale": "On the held-out test partition (n=87), the surrogate achieved MAE = 0.031 and R² = 0.974, satisfying both acceptance thresholds. Bland-Altman analysis showed no proportional bias. The comparison is limited to the nominal operating envelope represented in the training dataset."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Surrogate output quantity (RH) is the regulatory-relevant hemolysis metric for CPB device comparison.",
      "rationale": "The surrogate directly predicts the relative hemolysis index (RH), which is the primary quantity of interest for comparing CPB device hemolysis against a predicate device per the COU acceptance criterion (RH < 1). RH is computed from the power-law hemolysis model applied to CFD shear stress fields, and the surrogate maps design parameters directly to this scalar output."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities address the COU decision: identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device.",
      "rationale": "Validation activities demonstrate surrogate accuracy in ranking operating conditions by RH magnitude across the five nominal flow-speed combinations. The surrogate correctly identified the worst-case operating point (Q=2 L/min, N=4000 RPM, RH=0.87) in all five cross-validation folds. Validation is restricted to the nominal design space; no assessment was made for conditions outside the training envelope."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "CFD solver residuals for training-label simulations converge to below 1e-5 for all transport equations.",
      "rationale": "All 435 CFD simulations used to generate surrogate training labels achieved residual convergence below 1e-5 for continuity, momentum, and turbulence transport equations. The ML surrogate itself has no iterative solver; prediction is deterministic given fixed trained weights."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Surrogate deployment interface includes input range validation to prevent extrapolation beyond the training envelope.",
      "rationale": "The surrogate inference wrapper implements hard boundary checks on all eight input features (geometric dimensions and operating parameters). Inputs outside the training envelope trigger a warning and block prediction output. User documentation specifies the valid input ranges and the nominal-condition scope of the validation evidence."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Gradient boosting model form is appropriate for the hemolysis response surface given training data characteristics.",
      "rationale": "Gradient boosting was selected after comparison against linear regression, random forest, and shallow neural network architectures on the same training data. Cross-validated RMSE favored gradient boosting (RMSE=0.038) over the next-best architecture (random forest, RMSE=0.047). The non-parametric tree ensemble is consistent with the known nonlinear dependence of RH on tip clearance and rotational speed. Model form assessment is based solely on in-distribution performance."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Input features are physically motivated, measured with documented uncertainty, and span the nominal COU design space.",
      "rationale": "Eight input features were selected based on CFD sensitivity analysis and engineering judgment: impeller tip clearance, blade angle, rotational speed, flow rate, inlet diameter, outlet diameter, volute width, and blood viscosity. Feature measurement uncertainties are documented (tip clearance ±0.05 mm, rotational speed ±10 RPM). All inputs are within the nominal design space; no assessment of model behavior under degraded or uncertain inputs beyond nominal tolerances was conducted."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test partition is statistically independent from training data and representative of the nominal COU operating space.",
      "rationale": "The test partition (n=87, 20% stratified hold-out) was withheld prior to any model training or hyperparameter tuning. Stratification ensured proportional representation of all five flow-speed combinations. The test samples are drawn from the identical experimental and CFD campaign as the training data, spanning the same geometric and operating-condition envelope. No samples from alternative pump geometries, patient populations, or off-nominal conditions are included."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
